Project Name	Adlware
Project Description : This application is developed as a web based application so that multiple companies can use this application to manage their cases and patients. ADLWare is an application product designed to serve the end to end needs of the Home Health Care Industry and more specifically the Private Duty franchises, companies, agencies .The overall product has a core system like many of the competitive products and based on resource scheduling based on client needs. Service differentiation in this area is based on alerts and rapid response for missed schedules (shifts) .In this application clients are those who are receiving care and caregivers are those providing care and 
Case Managers are those responsible for working with and tracking the welfare and quality of life of clients under that care of companies caregivers. Telephony calls are also integrated with this web application with which by just pressing the numbers from the phone , caregivers can create the shift and can also clock in and clock out from their shifts.
Case manager creates the shift for a particular client and then allot the caregivers to the shifts and collect status information about their ADL (active daily living) including attitude, mobility, clarity, as well as the hygiene and care, the caregiver is providing.
The caregivers will log into the system via the clients telephone and also via their web enabled GPS phone which are integrated with our main ADLWare application and can also clock in and clock out through telephony call and gps enabled phone.
Both systems should track the user ID, client ID, Company ID, Caller ID, GPS location (if available) , and time when clocking-in.
When the shift is complete and the caregiver is clocking-out the same values are collected.
Billing is done by the system, the system generates the bill for the responsible party for the time spent and at the rate pre-set in the system.
The invoice is created by the system with the option to email directly to the client or print for the office staff to deliver
.Similalrly payroll is calculated for the caregivers on the basis of how many hours they have worked. If a shift was worked but the caregiver forgot to clock-in or out then office staff would review and manually correct the shift that would update the billing and the payroll.

Project Description:

This application is developed as a web based application so that multiple companies can use this application to manage their cases and patients. ADLWare is an application product designed to serve the end to end needs of the Home Health Care Industry and more specifically the Private Duty franchises, companies, agencies .The overall product has a core system like many of the competitive products and based on resource scheduling based on client needs. Service differentiation in this area is based on alerts and rapid response for missed schedules (shifts) .In this application clients are those who are receiving care and caregivers are those providing care and

Case Managers are those responsible for working with and tracking the welfare and quality of life of clients under that care of companies caregivers. Telephony calls are also integrated with this web application with which by just pressing the numbers from the phone , caregivers can create the shift and can also clock in and clock out from their shifts.

Case manager creates the shift for a particular client and then allot the caregivers to the shifts and collect status information about their ADL (active daily living) including attitude, mobility, clarity, as well as the hygiene and care, the caregiver is providing. The caregivers will log into the system via the clients telephone and also via their web enabled GPS phone which are integrated with our main ADLWare application and can also clock in and clock out through telephony call and gps enabled phone. Both systems should track the user ID, client ID, Company ID, Caller ID, GPS location (if available) , and time when "clocking-in". When the shift is complete and the caregiver is "clocking-out" the same values are collected. Billing is done by the system, the system generates the bill for the responsible party for the time spent and at the rate pre-set in the system. The invoice is created by the system with the option to email directly to the client or print for the office staff to deliver.Similalrly payroll is calculated for the caregivers on the basis of how many hours they have worked. If a shift was worked but the caregiver forgot to clock-in or out then office staff would review and manually correct the shift that would update the billing and the payroll.
